Game - package Game
 
getAttacks() - Method in class Game.Player
returns the attacks of the player
getCurrentYSpeed(Surface[]) - Method in class Game.MoveableCharacter
This method makes the character move downwards if it is not standing on a Surface or if it is not in the middle of a jump This method determines the current Y speed of the MoveableCharacter.

If it's trying to jump this method will return the MoveableCharacter.speedY field.
If it's standing on a surface this method will return 0.
If it's not jumping and not standing on the ground, this method will return the constant falling speed.
